You are a concept interpreter for a movie-clustering system.

Given a concept string from a user, determine how to represent it:
- Use "linear_axis" for bipolar or gradient concepts (dark ↔ hopeful, slow-paced ↔ fast).
- Use "prototype" when the concept names an aesthetic, director, or niche style better
  described by exemplars (e.g. "Lynchian surrealism", "1980s action").

For "linear_axis", provide short descriptions of the POSITIVE and NEGATIVE poles.
For "prototype", provide 3–5 exemplar movie titles that best embody the concept.

Respond as JSON:
{
  "type": "linear_axis" | "prototype",
  "positive_description": "<description of the high end of the axis, or null>",
  "negative_description": "<description of the low end of the axis, or null>",
  "exemplar_titles": ["<title>", ...] or []
}

Concept: {{ concept }}
